{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_f4613f4a0d7d440db20fe458","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tASDF specification and core schemas\n2\t===================================\n3\t![CI](https://github.com/asdf-format/asdf-standard/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg)\n4\t![Downstream](https://github.com/asdf-format/asdf-standard/actions/workflows/downstream.yml/badge.svg)\n5\t[![pre-commit](https://img.shields.io/badge/pre--commit-enabled-brightgreen?logo=pre-commit&logoColor=white)](https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit)\n6\t[![Code style: black](https://img.shields.io/badge/code%20style-black-000000.svg)](https://github.com/psf/black)\n7\t[![Imports: isort](https://img.shields.io/badge/%20imports-isort-%231674b1?style=flat&labelColor=ef8336)](https://pycqa.github.io/isort/)\n8\t[![DOI](https://zenodo.org/badge/18113139.svg)](https://zenodo.org/badge/latestdoi/18113139)\n9\t\n10\tThis document describes the Advanced Scientific Data Format (ASDF),\n11\tpronounced *AZ*-diff.  You can read the full specification at [the online documentation](http://asdf-standard.readthedocs.io/).\n12\t\n13\t> This is the **A**dvanced **S**cientific **D**ata **F**ormat - if you are looking for the **A**daptable **S**eismic **D**ata **F**ormat, go here: http://seismic-data.org/\n14\t\n15\t\n16\t## Contributing\n17\tPlease open a new [issue](https://github.com/spacetelescope/asdf-standard/issue) or new [pull request](https://github.com/spacetelescope/asdf-standard/pulls) for bugs, feedback, or new features you would like to see. If there is an issue you would like to work on, please leave a comment and we will be happy to assist. New contributions and contributors are very welcome!\n18\t\n19\tThere are two mailing lists for ASDF:\n20\t\n21\t* [asdf-users](https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/asdf-users)\n22\t* [asdf-developers](https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/asdf-developers)\n23\t\n24\t## Getting More Information\n25\t\n26\t* [FAQ page](https://github.com/spacetelescope/asdf-standard/wiki/FAQ) on the wiki.\n27\t* [ASDF: A new data format for astronomy](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ascom.2015.06.004), published in *Astronomy and Computing*:\n28\t\n29\t> Greenfield, P., Droettboom, M., & Bray, E. (2015). ASDF: A new data format for astronomy. *Astronomy and Computing*, 12: 240-251.\n30\t> doi:[10.1016/j.ascom.2015.06.004](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ascom.2015.06.004)\n31\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ae9983da-2a27-4005-ae76-4fdce045d255","uuid":"a83bcf2e-73ab-4129-aaba-312f549746c2","timestamp":"2026-04-09T00:21:28.400Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md","content":"ASDF specification and core schemas\n===================================\n![CI](https://github.com/asdf-format/asdf-standard/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg)\n![Downstream](https://github.com/asdf-format/asdf-standard/actions/workflows/downstream.yml/badge.svg)\n[![pre-commit](https://img.shields.io/badge/pre--commit-enabled-brightgreen?logo=pre-commit&logoColor=white)](https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit)\n[![Code style: black](https://img.shields.io/badge/code%20style-black-000000.svg)](https://github.com/psf/black)\n[![Imports: isort](https://img.shields.io/badge/%20imports-isort-%231674b1?style=flat&labelColor=ef8336)](https://pycqa.github.io/isort/)\n[![DOI](https://zenodo.org/badge/18113139.svg)](https://zenodo.org/badge/latestdoi/18113139)\n\nThis document describes the Advanced Scientific Data Format (ASDF),\npronounced *AZ*-diff.  You can read the full specification at [the online documentation](http://asdf-standard.readthedocs.io/).\n\n> This is the **A**dvanced **S**cientific **D**ata **F**ormat - if you are looking for the **A**daptable **S**eismic **D**ata **F**ormat, go here: http://seismic-data.org/\n\n\n## Contributing\nPlease open a new [issue](https://github.com/spacetelescope/asdf-standard/issue) or new [pull request](https://github.com/spacetelescope/asdf-standard/pulls) for bugs, feedback, or new features you would like to see. If there is an issue you would like to work on, please leave a comment and we will be happy to assist. New contributions and contributors are very welcome!\n\nThere are two mailing lists for ASDF:\n\n* [asdf-users](https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/asdf-users)\n* [asdf-developers](https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/asdf-developers)\n\n## Getting More Information\n\n* [FAQ page](https://github.com/spacetelescope/asdf-standard/wiki/FAQ) on the wiki.\n* [ASDF: A new data format for astronomy](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ascom.2015.06.004), published in *Astronomy and Computing*:\n\n> Greenfield, P., Droettboom, M., & Bray, E. (2015). ASDF: A new data format for astronomy. *Astronomy and Computing*, 12: 240-251.\n> doi:[10.1016/j.ascom.2015.06.004](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ascom.2015.06.004)\n","numLines":31,"startLine":1,"totalLines":31}}}
